IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: INVITE BELIEVING COMMUNITIES TO ENGAGE PEOPLE GROUPS WHERE THE GOOD NEWS OF JESUS IS NOT YET KNOWN.
IRS990.MissionDesc: AS PART OF GOD'S MISSION TO THE WORLD, FRONTIER FELLOWSHIP INVITES BELIEVING COMMUNITIES TO ENGAGE PEOPLE GROUPS WHERE THE GOOD NEWS OF JESUS AND HIS KINGDOM IS NOT YET KNOWN.
IRS990.Desc: FRONTIER FELLOWSHIP ACTS ON THE CONVICTION THAT INTRODUCING PEOPLE TO THE GOOD NEWS OF JESUS BRINGS SPIRITUAL AND SOCIAL FLOURISHING AND CULTIVATES FAITH WITHIN INDIVIDUALS LACKING ACCESS TO THE GOSPEL. STAFF AND BOARD MEMBERS MOBILIZE CHURCHES AND MISSION GROUPS BY PREACHING, TEACHING, CONSULTING, NETWORKING AND LEADING SHORT-TERM VISION TRIPS TO SERVE ALONGSIDE INDIGENOUS PARTNERS. THE NATIONAL OFFICE PROVIDES RESOURCES SUCH AS A QUARTERLY MAGAZINE (SENT TO 8,500 SUBSCRIBERS), MONTHLY EMAIL UPDATES (SENT TO 3,500 SUBSCRIBERS), A BLOG AND VARIOUS OTHER DIGITAL AND PRINT MATERIALS. IN THE LAST FISCAL YEAR, FRONTIER FELLOWSHIP RAISED $535,540.00 TO SUPPORT PROJECTS FOCUSED ON FRONTIER MISSION. FRONTIER FELLOWSHIP IS CURRENTLY WORKING TO EXPAND OUR TEAM AND WIDEN OUR NETWORKS IN ORDER TO MOBILIZE MORE CHURCHES. WE ARE ALSO GOING DEEPER IN OUR LEARNING RELATIONSHIPS WITH KEY GLOBAL PARTNERS, IN ORDER TO GO FARTHER IN OUR REACH TO NEW FRONTIER PEOPLES AND REGIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. THEREFORE, THE STATEMENTS DO NOT INCLUDE A PROVISION FOR INCOME TAXES. THE ORGANIZATION HAS NO UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME TAX IN 2022 AND 2021. THE ORGANIZATION REVIEWS INCOME TAX POSITIONS TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN IN INCOME TAX RETURNS TO DETERMINE IF THERE ARE ANY INCOME TAX UNCERTAINTIES. THIS INCLUDES POSITIONS THAT THE ENTITY IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES OR NOT SUBJECT TO INCOME TAXES ON UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME. THE ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZES TAX BENEFITS FROM UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS ONLY IF IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THE TAX POSITIONS WILL BE SUSTAINED ON EXAMINATION BY TAXING AUTHORITIES, BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITIONS. THE ORGANIZATION HAS IDENTIFIED NO SIGNIFICANT INCOME TAX UNCERTAINTIES. THE ORGANIZATION FILES INFORMATION RETURNS AS A TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATION. SHOULD THAT STATUS BE CHALLENGED IN THE FUTURE, ALL YEARS SINCE INCEPTION COULD BE SUBJECT TO REVIEW BY THE IRS.
